According to Palas, the EU should have paid us millions of euros, because the Czech Republic is far from ports.
In the end, the European Commission responded positively to the Czech demand and organized an invitation to tender for the purchase of wheat from countries without maritime access.
Grants for obtaining grants were proposed to the municipalities by the Ministry of Local Development, headed by Minister Pavel Němec (US-DEU), in particular, to be used to write applications for grants granted by Brussels.
The EU states: "The strange regulations are rare".
While the regulations often give rise to criticism in the Member States, according to many experts, the EU's efforts to regulate and improve the effectiveness of the functioning of the Union and in the field of its general development deserve more praise.
More serious is, for example, experts say, the problem of using EU subsidies for projects that have absolutely nothing to do with strengthening European integration, but which have been imposed by the Member States during the budgetary negotiations.
